Comment: Easily the best first move for white, though some people prefer the dubious 1. d4?.

An unorthodox move for white. I did this to throw off my opponent, since he probably knows the sicilian better than I do. As we'll see, my suspicions were correct, and once we leave the main-line sicilian, this guy has no idea what to do. Classic sign of a guy who memorizes openings but doesn't actually know how to play them.
